faceoff_positive.comments:
I received this product for free in exchange for my honest feedback. 

I started using the Estée Lauder Revitalizing Supreme+ Night Power Bounce Creme Moisturizer and overall, I'm impressed with the results. From the very first night, I noticed a visible difference in my skin's texture and hydration. When I woke up, my skin felt smoother and more supple, which was a pleasant surprise. However, there are a few drawbacks. The scent of the moisturizer is quite strong, which might be a turn-off for those who prefer fragrance-free products. Additionally, the formula is thick, which means it can take a bit longer to absorb fully into the skin. While this isn't necessarily a dealbreaker, it might not be ideal if you prefer lighter creams that don't feel as heavy on the face. Lastly, the price is on the higher side, which makes it a significant investment. 

In summary, if you're looking for a moisturizer that delivers noticeable results overnight and don't mind the strong scent or thicker texture, the Estée Lauder Revitalizing Supreme+ Night Power Bounce Creme Moisturizer is worth trying, provided you're okay with the splurge.
faceoff_positive.headline: It's good!

faceoff_negative.comments: I am a huge fan of Estée Lauder, so I was ecstatic when the Revitalizing Supreme+ Night Power Bounce Creme was gifted to me by Estée Lauder in exchange for my honest review. This cream moisturizer has the classic Estée Lauder scent and packaging that feels posh and elegant. I really like how thick the moisturizer is, the texture is whipped with structure and bounce and glides on the face beautifully. I found that makeup work beautifully overtop of this moisturizer, but as someone with dry skin, this wasn't my favorite product of theirs. When using this cream alone on a no makeup day, the product didn't lock in the moisture like I needed it to. After a few hours, I felt that my face was pretty dry and tight and I needed to reapply the product. That said, the Revitalizing Supreme+ Night Power Bounce Creme is extremely luxurious and I'm sure it will work wonders on oily/combination skin.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not for Dry Skin
